-- Serbia’s Agrobanka Plans Capital Increase in 2012, Beta Reports
-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 2011-12-22T06:49:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-22/serbia-s-agrobanka-plans-capital-increase-in-2012-beta-reports.html
Agrobanka AD Beograd (AGBN)  plans a 50
million-euro ($65.3 million) to 100 million-euro capital
increase next year,  Beta  news agency reported, citing the bank’s
executive board chairman.  The government, the single-biggest shareholder with a 20.1
percent stake that may be raised to 25 percent by the end of the
month, has given preliminary consent for the increase that aims
to boost Agrobanka’s capacity to finance agribusinesses, the
report quoted Dusan Antonic as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
 msavic2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  